{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":261,"text":"I'm the luckiest guy in the world."},{"time":2944,"text":"I got to see the last case\nof killer smallpox in the world."},{"time":8182,"text":"I was in India this past year,"},{"time":10127,"text":"and I may have seen\nthe last cases of polio in the world."},{"time":15395,"text":"There's nothing that makes\nyou feel more --"},{"time":18440,"text":"the blessing and the honor\nof working in a program like that --"},{"time":23007,"text":"than to know that something\nthat horrible no longer exists."},{"time":27401,"text":"So I'm going to tell you --"},{"time":28752,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":31481,"text":"so I'm going to show you\nsome dirty pictures."},{"time":34314,"text":"They are difficult to watch,\nbut you should look at them with optimism,"},{"time":40688,"text":"because the horror\nof these pictures will be matched"},{"time":45783,"text":"by the uplifting quality of knowing\nthat they no longer exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50839,"text":"But first, I'm going to tell you\na little bit about my own journey."},{"time":55455,"text":"My background is not exactly\nthe conventional medical education"},{"time":58764,"text":"that you might expect."},{"time":61230,"text":"When I was an intern in San Francisco,"},{"time":66163,"text":"I heard about a group of Native Americans\nwho had taken over Alcatraz Island,"},{"time":69999,"text":"and a Native American\nwho wanted to give birth on that island,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and no other doctor wanted\nto go and help her give birth."},{"time":77165,"text":"I went out to Alcatraz, and I lived\non the island for several weeks."},{"time":81588,"text":"She gave birth; I caught\nthe baby; I got off the island;"},{"time":84333,"text":"I landed in San Francisco;"},{"time":86213,"text":"and all the press wanted to talk to me,"},{"time":88125,"text":"because my three weeks on the island\nmade me an expert in Indian affairs."},{"time":92250,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":93278,"text":"I wound up on every television show."},{"time":95341,"text":"Someone saw me on television;\nthey called me up; and they asked me"},{"time":98477,"text":"if I'd like to be in a movie\nand to play a young doctor"},{"time":101106,"text":"for a bunch of rock and roll stars\nwho were traveling in a bus ride"},{"time":104280,"text":"from San Francisco to England."},{"time":106378,"text":"And I said, yes, I would do that,"},{"time":108000,"text":"so I became the doctor\nin an absolutely awful movie"},{"time":112280,"text":"called \"Medicine Ball Caravan.\""},{"time":114202,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":115272,"text":"Now, you know from the '60s,"},{"time":116768,"text":"you're either on the bus\nor you're off the bus; I was on the bus."},{"time":119869,"text":"My wife of 37 years and I joined the bus."},{"time":122890,"text":"Our bus ride took us\nfrom San Francisco to London,"},{"time":125594,"text":"then we switched buses at the big pond."},{"time":127817,"text":"We then got on two more buses"},{"time":131269,"text":"and we drove through Turkey\nand Iran, Afghanistan,"},{"time":134365,"text":"over the Khyber Pass into Pakistan,\nlike every other young doctor."},{"time":138000,"text":"This is us at the Khyber Pass,\nand that's our bus."},{"time":140691,"text":"We had some difficulty getting\nover the Khyber Pass."},{"time":144529,"text":"But we wound up in India."},{"time":146465,"text":"And then, like everyone else\nin our generation,"},{"time":148738,"text":"we went to live in a Himalayan monastery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151047,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154420,"text":"This is just like a residency program,"},{"time":156255,"text":"for those of you\nthat are in medical school."},{"time":158435,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":160092,"text":"And we studied with a wise man,\na guru named Karoli Baba,"},{"time":165316,"text":"who then told me to get rid of the dress,"},{"time":168982,"text":"put on a three-piece suit,"},{"time":170749,"text":"go join the United Nations as a diplomat"},{"time":174027,"text":"and work for the World\nHealth Organization."},{"time":176111,"text":"And he made an outrageous prediction\nthat smallpox would be eradicated,"},{"time":180503,"text":"and that this was God's gift to humanity,"},{"time":183549,"text":"because of the hard work\nof dedicated scientists."},{"time":186660,"text":"And that prediction came true."},{"time":189504,"text":"This little girl is Rahima Banu,"},{"time":191838,"text":"and she was the last case\nof killer smallpox in the world."},{"time":195232,"text":"And this document is the certificate\nthat the global commission signed,"},{"time":200232,"text":"certifying the world to have eradicated\nthe first disease in history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206336,"text":"The key to eradicating smallpox\nwas early detection, early response."},{"time":212661,"text":"I'm going to ask you to repeat that:\nearly detection, early response."},{"time":216692,"text":"Can you say that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217868,"text":"Audience: Early detection, early response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220962,"text":"Larry Brilliant: Smallpox\nwas the worst disease in history."},{"time":223895,"text":"It killed more people\nthan all the wars in history."},{"time":226437,"text":"In the last century,\nit killed 500 million people."},{"time":232943,"text":"You're reading about Larry Page already."},{"time":234873,"text":"Somebody reads very fast."},{"time":236469,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":238047,"text":"In the year that Larry Page\nand Sergey Brin --"},{"time":240245,"text":"with whom I have a certain affection\nand a new affiliation --"},{"time":243885,"text":"in the year in which they were born,"},{"time":246089,"text":"two million people died of smallpox."},{"time":249059,"text":"We declared smallpox eradicated in 1980."},{"time":253760,"text":"This is the most important slide\nthat I've ever seen in public health,"},{"time":257080,"text":"[Sovereigns killed by smallpox]\nbecause it shows you"},{"time":259588,"text":"to be the richest and the strongest,"},{"time":261483,"text":"and to be kings and queens of the world,"},{"time":263432,"text":"did not protect you\nfrom dying of smallpox."},{"time":265530,"text":"Never can you doubt\nthat we are all in this together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270469,"text":"But to see smallpox\nfrom the perspective of a sovereign"},{"time":274403,"text":"is the wrong perspective."},{"time":276302,"text":"You should see it\nfrom the perspective of a mother,"},{"time":279000,"text":"watching her child develop\nthis disease and standing by helplessly."},{"time":282841,"text":"Day one, day two, day three,"},{"time":288596,"text":"day four, day five, day six."},{"time":294701,"text":"You're a mother and you're\nwatching your child,"},{"time":297638,"text":"and on day six, you see\npustules that become hard."},{"time":303400,"text":"Day seven, they show the classic scars\nof smallpox umbilication."},{"time":308148,"text":"Day eight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309482,"text":"And Al Gore said earlier"},{"time":311234,"text":"that the most photographed\nimage in the world,"},{"time":314147,"text":"the most printed image in the world,"},{"time":315918,"text":"was that of the Earth."},{"time":317516,"text":"But this was in 1974,\nand as of that moment,"},{"time":320737,"text":"this photograph was the photograph\nthat was the most widely printed,"},{"time":324384,"text":"because we printed two billion copies\nof this photograph,"},{"time":327893,"text":"and we took them\nhand to hand, door to door,"},{"time":331071,"text":"to show people and ask them\nif there was smallpox in their house,"},{"time":335976,"text":"because that was our surveillance system."},{"time":338106,"text":"We didn't have Google,\nwe didn't have web crawlers,"},{"time":340685,"text":"we didn't have computers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343867,"text":"By day nine -- you look at this picture\nand you're horrified;"},{"time":347748,"text":"I look at this picture\nand I say, \"Thank God,\""},{"time":350305,"text":"because it's clear that this is only\nan ordinary case of smallpox,"},{"time":354290,"text":"and I know this child will live."},{"time":357487,"text":"And by day 13, the lesions\nare scabbing, his eyelids are swollen,"},{"time":362854,"text":"but you know this child has\nno other secondary infection."},{"time":367064,"text":"And by day 20, while he will be\nscarred for life, he will live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372175,"text":"There are other kinds of smallpox\nthat are not like that."},{"time":375248,"text":"This is confluent smallpox,"},{"time":377660,"text":"in which there isn't a single place\non the body where you could put a finger"},{"time":381469,"text":"and not be covered by lesions."},{"time":384302,"text":"Flat smallpox, which killed 100 percent\nof people who got it."},{"time":388612,"text":"And hemorrhagic smallpox,\nthe most cruel of all,"},{"time":391605,"text":"which had a predilection\nfor pregnant women."},{"time":394897,"text":"I've probably had 50 women die."},{"time":397310,"text":"They all had hemorrhagic smallpox."},{"time":399436,"text":"I've never seen anybody die from it\nwho wasn't a pregnant woman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403458,"text":"In 1967, the WHO embarked\non what was an outrageous program"},{"time":407403,"text":"to eradicate a disease."},{"time":409204,"text":"In that year, there were 34 countries\naffected with smallpox."},{"time":413363,"text":"By 1970, we were down to 18 countries."},{"time":416848,"text":"1974, we were down to five countries."},{"time":419848,"text":"But in that year,\nsmallpox exploded throughout India."},{"time":425154,"text":"And India was the place\nwhere smallpox made its last stand."},{"time":429548,"text":"In 1974, India had\na population of 600 million."},{"time":432611,"text":"There are 21 linguistic states in India,"},{"time":435653,"text":"which is like saying\n21 different countries."},{"time":438242,"text":"There are 20 million people\non the road at any time,"},{"time":441163,"text":"in buses and trains, walking;\n500,000 villages, 120 million households,"},{"time":447206,"text":"and none of them wanted to report"},{"time":449534,"text":"if they had a case\nof smallpox in their house,"},{"time":452000,"text":"because they thought that smallpox\nwas the visitation of a deity,"},{"time":455388,"text":"Shitala Mata, the cooling mother,"},{"time":457435,"text":"and it was wrong to bring\nstrangers into your house"},{"time":461635,"text":"when the deity was in the house."},{"time":464048,"text":"No incentive to report smallpox."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466686,"text":"It wasn't just India\nthat had smallpox deities;"},{"time":469315,"text":"smallpox deities were\nprevalent all over the world."},{"time":473000,"text":"So, how we eradicated smallpox was --"},{"time":476436,"text":"mass vaccination wouldn't work."},{"time":478734,"text":"You could vaccinate everybody in India,"},{"time":480661,"text":"but one year later there'd be\n21 million new babies,"},{"time":483185,"text":"which was then the population of Canada."},{"time":485693,"text":"It wouldn't do just to vaccinate everyone."},{"time":487905,"text":"You had to find every single\ncase of smallpox in the world"},{"time":491000,"text":"at the same time, and draw\na circle of immunity around it."},{"time":494545,"text":"And that's what we did."},{"time":497315,"text":"In India alone, my 150,000 best friends\nand I went door to door,"},{"time":502534,"text":"with that same picture,"},{"time":504632,"text":"to every single house in India."},{"time":506227,"text":"We made over one billion house calls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509541,"text":"And in the process,\nI learned something very important."},{"time":513763,"text":"Every time we did a house-to-house search,"},{"time":518045,"text":"we had a spike in the number\nof reports of smallpox."},{"time":522793,"text":"When we didn't search, we had\nthe illusion that there was no disease."},{"time":527952,"text":"When we did search, we had the illusion\nthat there was more disease."},{"time":532180,"text":"A surveillance system was necessary,"},{"time":534443,"text":"because what we needed\nwas early detection, early response."},{"time":541722,"text":"So we searched and we searched,"},{"time":543945,"text":"and we found every case\nof smallpox in India."},{"time":546819,"text":"We had a reward. We raised the reward."},{"time":549804,"text":"We continued to increase the reward."},{"time":551884,"text":"We had a scorecard\nthat we wrote on every house."},{"time":555426,"text":"And as we did that,"},{"time":557181,"text":"the number of reported cases\nin the world dropped to zero."},{"time":561963,"text":"And in 1980, we declared the globe\nfree of smallpox."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566667,"text":"It was the largest campaign\nin United Nations history,"},{"time":571196,"text":"until the Iraq war."},{"time":573657,"text":"150,000 people from all over the world --"},{"time":577000,"text":"doctors of every race,\nreligion, culture and nation,"},{"time":579940,"text":"who fought side by side,\nbrothers and sisters,"},{"time":584859,"text":"with each other, not against each other,"},{"time":588121,"text":"in a common cause\nto make the world better."},{"time":591248,"text":"But smallpox was the fourth disease\nthat was intended for eradication."},{"time":595068,"text":"We failed three other times."},{"time":597345,"text":"We failed against malaria,\nyellow fever and yaws."},{"time":600648,"text":"But soon we may see polio eradicated."},{"time":604000,"text":"But the key to eradicating polio\nis early detection, early response."},{"time":610610,"text":"This may be the year we eradicate polio."},{"time":613483,"text":"That will make it\nthe second disease in history."},{"time":616197,"text":"And David Heymann, who's watching\nthis on the webcast --"},{"time":620360,"text":"David, keep on going. We're close!"},{"time":623344,"text":"We're down to four countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631431,"text":"I feel like Hank Aaron."},{"time":632670,"text":"Barry Bonds can replace me any time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634697,"text":"Let's get another disease off the list\nof terrible things to worry about."},{"time":639815,"text":"I was just in India working on\nthe polio program."},{"time":643088,"text":"The polio surveillance program\nis four million people going door to door."},{"time":648875,"text":"That is the surveillance system."},{"time":651000,"text":"But we need to have\nearly detection, early response."},{"time":655150,"text":"Blindness, the same thing."},{"time":656801,"text":"The key to discovering blindness\nis doing epidemiological surveys"},{"time":661777,"text":"and finding out the causes of blindness,"},{"time":664000,"text":"so you can mount the correct response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667261,"text":"The Seva Foundation\nwas started by a group of alumni"},{"time":671898,"text":"of the Smallpox Eradication Programme,"},{"time":674814,"text":"who, having climbed the highest mountain,"},{"time":677529,"text":"tasted the elixir of the success\nof eradicating a disease,"},{"time":682000,"text":"wanted to do it again."},{"time":684000,"text":"And over the last 27 years,\nSeva's programs in 15 countries"},{"time":688892,"text":"have given back sight\nto more than two million blind people."},{"time":692982,"text":"Seva got started because we wanted\nto apply these lessons"},{"time":696137,"text":"of surveillance and epidemiology"},{"time":698756,"text":"to something which nobody else\nwas looking at as a public health issue:"},{"time":702705,"text":"blindness, which heretofore had been\nthought of only as a clinical disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707834,"text":"In 1980, Steve Jobs gave me\nthat computer, which is Apple number 12,"},{"time":714130,"text":"and it's still in Kathmandu,\nand it's still working,"},{"time":716607,"text":"and we ought to go get it and auction\nit off and make more money for Seva."},{"time":721214,"text":"And we conducted the first Nepal survey\never done for health,"},{"time":725274,"text":"and the first nationwide\nblindness survey ever done,"},{"time":728155,"text":"and we had astonishing results."},{"time":730562,"text":"Instead of finding out\nwhat we thought was the case --"},{"time":733297,"text":"that blindness was caused mostly\nby glaucoma and trachoma --"},{"time":737000,"text":"we were astounded to find out"},{"time":739488,"text":"that blindness was caused\ninstead by cataract."},{"time":744092,"text":"You can't cure or prevent\nwhat you don't know is there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750145,"text":"In your TED packages\nthere's a DVD, \"Infinite Vision,\""},{"time":754365,"text":"about Dr. V and the Aravind Eye Hospital."},{"time":757000,"text":"I hope that you will take a look at it."},{"time":759056,"text":"Aravind, which started as a Seva project,"},{"time":761254,"text":"is now the world's largest\nand best eye hospital."},{"time":764226,"text":"This year, that one hospital\nwill give back sight"},{"time":767647,"text":"to more than 300,000 people\nin Tamil Nadu, India."},{"time":771222,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":775520,"text":"Bird flu."},{"time":776696,"text":"I stand here as a representative\nof all terrible things --"},{"time":779541,"text":"this might be the worst."},{"time":781791,"text":"The key to preventing\nor mitigating pandemic bird flu"},{"time":786569,"text":"is early detection and rapid response."},{"time":789000,"text":"We will not have a vaccine\nor adequate supplies of an antiviral"},{"time":794827,"text":"to combat bird flu if it occurs\nin the next three years."},{"time":798342,"text":"WHO stages the progress of a pandemic."},{"time":802346,"text":"We are now at stage three\non the pandemic alert stage,"},{"time":806763,"text":"with just a little bit\nof human-to-human transmission,"},{"time":810342,"text":"but no human-to-human-to-human\nsustained transmission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"The moment WHO says\nwe've moved to category four --"},{"time":818252,"text":"this will not be like Katrina."},{"time":820439,"text":"The world as we know it will stop."},{"time":822542,"text":"There'll be no airplanes flying."},{"time":825000,"text":"Would you get in an airplane\nwith 250 people you didn't know,"},{"time":828173,"text":"coughing and sneezing,"},{"time":829349,"text":"when you knew that some of them\nmight carry a disease that could kill you,"},{"time":832866,"text":"for which you had\nno antivirals or vaccine?"},{"time":836877,"text":"I did a study of the top epidemiologists\nin the world in October."},{"time":840918,"text":"I asked them -- these are all fluologists\nand specialists in influenza --"},{"time":845000,"text":"and I asked them the questions\nyou'd like to ask them:"},{"time":847860,"text":"What do you think the likelihood\nis that there'll be a pandemic?"},{"time":851072,"text":"If it happens, how bad\ndo you think it will be?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":854622,"text":"Fifteen percent said they thought\nthere'd be a pandemic within three years."},{"time":858737,"text":"But much worse than that,"},{"time":860697,"text":"90 percent said they thought\nthere'd be a pandemic"},{"time":864183,"text":"within your children\nor your grandchildren's lifetime."},{"time":868247,"text":"And they thought\nthat if there was a pandemic,"},{"time":871795,"text":"a billion people would get sick."},{"time":874723,"text":"As many as 165 million people would die."},{"time":878850,"text":"There would be a global\nrecession and depression"},{"time":881390,"text":"as our just-in-time inventory system"},{"time":883592,"text":"and the tight rubber band\nof globalization broke,"},{"time":887434,"text":"and the cost to our economy\nof one to three trillion dollars"},{"time":891402,"text":"would be far worse for everyone\nthan merely 100 million people dying,"},{"time":897048,"text":"because so many more people\nwould lose their job"},{"time":899374,"text":"and their healthcare benefits,"},{"time":901000,"text":"that the consequences\nare almost unthinkable."},{"time":905169,"text":"And it's getting worse,\nbecause travel is getting so much better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911210,"text":"Let me show you a simulation\nof what a pandemic looks like."},{"time":917746,"text":"So we know what we're talking about."},{"time":920393,"text":"Let's assume, for example,\nthat the first case occurs in South Asia."},{"time":925400,"text":"It initially goes quite slowly."},{"time":927774,"text":"You get two or three discrete locations."},{"time":932128,"text":"Then there'll be secondary outbreaks,\nand the disease will spread"},{"time":936765,"text":"from country to country so fast\nthat you won't know what hit you."},{"time":941510,"text":"Within three weeks\nit will be everywhere in the world."},{"time":945786,"text":"Now, if we had an \"undo\" button,\nand we could go back and isolate it"},{"time":951161,"text":"and grab it when it first started --\nif we could find it early,"},{"time":954542,"text":"and we had early detection\nand early response,"},{"time":957000,"text":"and we could put each one\nof those viruses in jail --"},{"time":960714,"text":"that's the only way to deal with\nsomething like a pandemic."},{"time":967349,"text":"And let me show you why that is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970095,"text":"We have a joke."},{"time":971279,"text":"This is an epidemic curve,\nand everyone in medicine,"},{"time":974127,"text":"I think, ultimately gets\nto know what it is."},{"time":976574,"text":"But the joke is,"},{"time":977752,"text":"an epidemiologist likes to arrive\nat an epidemic right here"},{"time":980885,"text":"and ride to glory on the downhill curve."},{"time":983047,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":984174,"text":"But you don't get to do that usually."},{"time":986000,"text":"You usually arrive right about here."},{"time":988525,"text":"What we really want is to arrive\nright here, so we can stop the epidemic."},{"time":994325,"text":"But you can't always do that."},{"time":996192,"text":"But there's an organization\nthat has been able to find a way"},{"time":999773,"text":"to learn when the first cases occur,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"and that is called GPHIN;"},{"time":1004373,"text":"it's the Global Public Health\nInformation Network."},{"time":1007246,"text":"And that simulation that I showed you"},{"time":1009358,"text":"that you thought\nwas bird flu -- that was SARS."},{"time":1011963,"text":"And SARS is the pandemic\nthat did not occur."},{"time":1015332,"text":"And it didn't occur"},{"time":1016755,"text":"because GPHIN found\nthe pandemic-to-be of SARS"},{"time":1023090,"text":"three months before WHO actually\nannounced it, and because of that,"},{"time":1029152,"text":"we were able to stop the SARS pandemic."},{"time":1032342,"text":"And I think we owe\na great debt of gratitude"},{"time":1034447,"text":"to GPHIN and to Ron St. John,"},{"time":1036628,"text":"who I hope is in the audience\nsome place -- over there --"},{"time":1040103,"text":"who's the founder of GPHIN."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043507,"text":"Hello, Ron!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053610,"text":"And TED has flown Ron here\nfrom Ottawa, where GPHIN is located,"},{"time":1058248,"text":"because not only\ndid GPHIN find SARS early,"},{"time":1062709,"text":"but you may have seen last week"},{"time":1064850,"text":"that Iran announced\nthat they had bird flu in Iran,"},{"time":1069205,"text":"but GPHIN found the bird flu\nin Iran not February 14 --"},{"time":1072921,"text":"but last September."},{"time":1074802,"text":"We need an early-warning system"},{"time":1077486,"text":"to protect us against the things\nthat are humanity's worst nightmare."},{"time":1082639,"text":"And so my TED wish is based on\nthe common denominator"},{"time":1086465,"text":"of these experiences."},{"time":1087855,"text":"Smallpox -- early detection,\nearly response."},{"time":1090765,"text":"Blindness, polio --\nearly detection, early response."},{"time":1094249,"text":"Pandemic bird flu --\nearly detection, early response."},{"time":1098265,"text":"It is a litany."},{"time":1099676,"text":"It is so obvious that our only way\nof dealing with these new diseases"},{"time":1104714,"text":"is to find them early\nand to kill them before they spread."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109065,"text":"So, my TED wish is for you\nto help build a global system --"},{"time":1113497,"text":"an early-warning system --"},{"time":1115000,"text":"to protect us against\nhumanity's worst nightmares."},{"time":1119381,"text":"And what I thought I would call it\nis \"Early Detection,\""},{"time":1126724,"text":"But it should really be called ..."},{"time":1130223,"text":"\"Total Early Detection.\"\n[TED]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131896,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1133003,"text":"What?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134178,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1141593,"text":"What?"},{"time":1142767,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1146219,"text":"But in all seriousness,"},{"time":1148086,"text":"because this idea is birthed in TED,"},{"time":1151633,"text":"I would like it to be\na legacy of TED, and I'd like to call it"},{"time":1157000,"text":"the \"International System for Total\nEarly Disease Detection.\""},{"time":1162245,"text":"[INSTEDD]"},{"time":1165800,"text":"And INSTEDD then becomes our mantra."},{"time":1173235,"text":"So instead of a hidden\npandemic of bird flu,"},{"time":1175764,"text":"we find it and immediately contain it."},{"time":1178723,"text":"Instead of a novel virus\ncaused by bio-terror or bio-error,"},{"time":1183622,"text":"or shift or drift,\nwe find it and we contain it."},{"time":1188268,"text":"Instead of industrial\naccidents like oil spills"},{"time":1190778,"text":"or the catastrophe in Bhopal,"},{"time":1193000,"text":"we find them, and we respond to them."},{"time":1196790,"text":"Instead of famine,\nhidden until it is too late,"},{"time":1199937,"text":"we detect it, and we respond."},{"time":1204061,"text":"And instead of a system\nwhich is owned by a government,"},{"time":1207252,"text":"and hidden in the bowels of government,"},{"time":1209697,"text":"let's build an early detection system"},{"time":1212323,"text":"that's freely available to anyone\nin the world in their own language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1216858,"text":"Let's make it transparent,\nnon-governmental,"},{"time":1221650,"text":"not owned by any single\ncountry or company,"},{"time":1224730,"text":"housed in a neutral country,\nwith redundant backup"},{"time":1228174,"text":"in a different time zone\nand a different continent."},{"time":1232135,"text":"And let's build it on GPHIN."},{"time":1234152,"text":"Let's start with GPHIN."},{"time":1236050,"text":"Let's increase the websites\nthat they crawl"},{"time":1238988,"text":"from 20,000 to 20 million."},{"time":1241498,"text":"Let's increase the languages they crawl"},{"time":1244031,"text":"from seven to 70, or more."},{"time":1247173,"text":"Let's build in outbound\nconfirmation messages,"},{"time":1250737,"text":"using text messages or SMS\nor instant messaging"},{"time":1254025,"text":"to find out from people\nwho are within 100 meters"},{"time":1256859,"text":"of the rumor that you hear,"},{"time":1258634,"text":"if it is, in fact, valid."},{"time":1260000,"text":"And let's add satellite confirmation."},{"time":1262614,"text":"And we'll add Gapminder's\namazing graphics to the front end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1266545,"text":"And we'll grow it\nas a moral force in the world,"},{"time":1270487,"text":"finding out those terrible things"},{"time":1272603,"text":"before anybody else knows about them,"},{"time":1274714,"text":"and sending our response to them,"},{"time":1277164,"text":"so that next year,\ninstead of us meeting here,"},{"time":1280702,"text":"lamenting how many terrible things\nthere are in the world,"},{"time":1284280,"text":"we will have pulled together,"},{"time":1286042,"text":"used the unique skills\nand the magic of this community,"},{"time":1290945,"text":"and be proud that we have done\neverything we can to stop pandemics,"},{"time":1294391,"text":"other catastrophes, and change\nthe world, beginning right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1300083,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1318991,"text":"Chris Anderson: An amazing presentation."},{"time":1321200,"text":"First of all, just so\neveryone understands:"},{"time":1324007,"text":"you're saying that\nby creating web crawlers,"},{"time":1328547,"text":"looking on the Internet for patterns,"},{"time":1331452,"text":"they can detect something suspicious"},{"time":1335881,"text":"before WHO, before anyone else can see it?"},{"time":1339478,"text":"Give an example of how\nthat could possibly be true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1343174,"text":"Larry Brilliant: You're not mad\nabout the copyright violation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1346135,"text":"CA: No. I love it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1347318,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1348544,"text":"LB: Well, as Ron St. John --"},{"time":1350121,"text":"I hope you'll go and meet him\nin the dinner afterwards and talk to him."},{"time":1353565,"text":"When he started GPHIN --"},{"time":1356142,"text":"In 1997, there was an outbreak\nof bird flu -- H5N1."},{"time":1360562,"text":"It was in Hong Kong."},{"time":1361873,"text":"And a remarkable doctor in Hong Kong\nresponded immediately,"},{"time":1365079,"text":"by slaughtering 1.5 million\nchickens and birds,"},{"time":1369920,"text":"and they stopped\nthat outbreak in its tracks."},{"time":1372832,"text":"Immediate detection, immediate response."},{"time":1376068,"text":"Then a number of years went by,"},{"time":1377586,"text":"and there were a lot\nof rumors about bird flu."},{"time":1380584,"text":"Ron and his team in Ottawa\nbegan to crawl the web --"},{"time":1384396,"text":"only crawling 20,000 different websites,\nmostly periodicals --"},{"time":1389610,"text":"and they read about\nand heard about a concern,"},{"time":1392857,"text":"of a lot of children who had high fever\nand symptoms of bird flu."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1397613,"text":"They reported this to WHO."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1400161,"text":"WHO took a little while taking action,"},{"time":1402197,"text":"because WHO will only receive\na report from a government,"},{"time":1406880,"text":"because it's the United Nations."},{"time":1409396,"text":"But they were able to point\nto WHO and let them know"},{"time":1412822,"text":"that there was this surprising\nand unexplained cluster of illnesses"},{"time":1417311,"text":"that looked like bird flu."},{"time":1419080,"text":"That turned out to be SARS."},{"time":1420838,"text":"That's how the world found out about SARS."},{"time":1423805,"text":"And because of that,\nwe were able to stop SARS."},{"time":1426739,"text":"Now, what's really important is that,\nbefore there was GPHIN,"},{"time":1430341,"text":"100 percent of all the world's\nreports of bad things --"},{"time":1434580,"text":"whether you're talking about famine"},{"time":1436272,"text":"or you're talking about bird flu\nor you're talking about Ebola --"},{"time":1439374,"text":"100 percent of all those reports\ncame from nations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1442526,"text":"The moment these guys in Ottawa --"},{"time":1444209,"text":"on a budget of 800,000 dollars\na year -- got cracking,"},{"time":1448614,"text":"75 percent of all the reports\nin the world came from GPHIN,"},{"time":1452770,"text":"25 percent of all the reports in the world"},{"time":1455158,"text":"came from all the other 180 nations."},{"time":1458516,"text":"Now, here's what's really interesting:"},{"time":1460508,"text":"after they'd been working\nfor a couple years,"},{"time":1463175,"text":"what do you think happened\nto those nations?"},{"time":1465297,"text":"They felt pretty stupid."},{"time":1466504,"text":"So they started sending in\ntheir reports early."},{"time":1468741,"text":"And now, their reporting percentage\nis down to 50 percent,"},{"time":1472621,"text":"because other nations\nhave started to report."},{"time":1475063,"text":"So, can you find diseases\nearly by crawling the web?"},{"time":1479253,"text":"Of course you can."},{"time":1480825,"text":"Can you find it even earlier\nthan GPHIN does now?"},{"time":1483697,"text":"Of course you can."},{"time":1484872,"text":"You saw that they found SARS\nusing their Chinese web crawler"},{"time":1489501,"text":"a full six weeks before they found it\nusing their English web crawler."},{"time":1494793,"text":"Well, they're only crawling\nin seven languages."},{"time":1497206,"text":"These bad viruses really\ndon't have any intention"},{"time":1499736,"text":"of showing up first in English\nor Spanish or French."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1502218,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1504241,"text":"So yes, I want to take GPHIN,\nI want to build on it."},{"time":1509312,"text":"I want to add all the languages\nof the world that we possibly can."},{"time":1512688,"text":"I want to make this open to everybody,"},{"time":1515000,"text":"so that the health officer\nin Nairobi or in Patna, Bihar"},{"time":1518000,"text":"will have as much access to it\nas the folks in Ottawa or in CDC."},{"time":1522724,"text":"And I want to make it part of our culture"},{"time":1525152,"text":"that there is a community of people\nwho are watching out"},{"time":1528763,"text":"for the worst nightmares of humanity,"},{"time":1531000,"text":"and that it's accessible to everyone."}]}]}